main_body:
Regulations (EC) No 1866/95, (EC) No 2497/96, (EC) No 1899/97 and (EC) No 1396/98 are amended as follows:
(a) Article 4(1) is replaced by the following: "1. Licence applications shall be lodged during the first seven days of the month preceding each period as specified in Article 2.";
(b) The following paragraph 8 is added to Article 4: "8. Member States shall notify the Commission, before the end of the fourth month following each annual period specified in Annex I, of the total volume of products imported for each of the groups under this Regulation during that period.
All notifications, including 'nil' ones, shall be made using the model in Annex IV to this Regulation.";
(c) The following is added to the first paragraph of Article 5: "However, the validity of licences shall not extend beyond the end of the last period of the year referred to in Article 2 for which a licence has been issued."
